com.geoloqi.android.sdk
Class LQSharedPreferences

java.lang.Object
  com.geoloqi.android.sdk.LQSharedPreferences

public class LQSharedPreferences
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains a collection of static methods for reading and writing key/value data required by the Geoloqi SDK.

Getters are provided for reading client preferences and other important data required for authenticating with the Geoloqi API. Data may be read from a geoloqi.properties file included in the client application's assets directory.

Setters are provided for updating preference values and for providing values when a geoloqi.properties file is not included.

Any values set in a geoloqi.properties asset will take precedence over values set using the provided setter methods.

Author:
Tristan Waddington

enablePushNotificationHandling

public static boolean enablePushNotificationHandling(android.content.Context context)

Call this method to enable the default handling of push messages by the location service.

If push message handling is enabled, the location service will automatically create a status bar notification. This is the default behavior.

See also:

  • disablePushNotificationHandling(android.content.Context)
  • isPushNotificationHandlingEnabled(android.content.Context)

Parameters:
context -
Returns:
true if the new value was successfully written to SharedPreferences.

disablePushNotificationHandling

public static boolean disablePushNotificationHandling(android.content.Context context)

Call this method to disable the default handling of push messages by the location service.

If push message handling is disabled, the location service will still receive push messages, but will not automatically create a status bar notification. This will allow you to manually handle incoming push messages.

To manually handle push messages you can should:

  • Subclass LQBroadcastReceiver and implement the abstract method LQBroadcastReceiver.onPushMessageReceived(android.content.Context, android.os.Bundle).
  • Register your broadcast receiver to Listen for the LQBroadcastReceiver.ACTION_PUSH_MESSAGE_RECEIVED broadcast intent.

See also:

  • enablePushNotificationHandling(android.content.Context)
  • isPushNotificationHandlingEnabled(android.content.Context)

Parameters:
context -
Returns:
true if the new value was successfully written to SharedPreferences.

enableLowBatteryTracking

public static boolean enableLowBatteryTracking(android.content.Context context)

Call this method to enable low battery tracking. This means that the location service should continue functioning even when the device indicates that the battery has reached a dangerously low level.

Enabling low battery tracking is not the default and should be avoided unless the client is implementing a dedicated logging application.

See also:

  • disableLowBatteryTracking(android.content.Context)
  • isLowBatteryTrackingEnabled(android.content.Context)

Parameters:
context -
Returns:
true if the new value was successfully written to SharedPreferences.

disableLowBatteryTracking

public static boolean disableLowBatteryTracking(android.content.Context context)

Call this method to disable low battery tracking. This means that the location service should suspend when the device indicates that it has a lower battery. The service will automatically resume when the device has returned to a safe power level.

See also:

  • enableLowBatteryTracking(android.content.Context)
  • isLowBatteryTrackingEnabled(android.content.Context)

Parameters:
context -
Returns:
true if the new value was successfully written to SharedPreferences.

isLowBatteryTrackingEnabled

public static boolean isLowBatteryTrackingEnabled(android.content.Context context)

See also:

  • disableLowBatteryTracking(android.content.Context)
  • enableLowBatteryTracking(android.content.Context)

Parameters:
context -
